---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="velocitybench - GraphQL Benchmarking Suite | FraiseQL"
  description="Comprehensive GraphQL framework benchmarking suite. Compare 28+ frameworks across performance, memory, and scalability metrics."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>⚡ velocitybench</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>GraphQL Benchmarking Suite</strong> – 28 frameworks compared
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>What It Does</h2>
      <p>
        velocitybench is a comprehensive benchmarking suite for GraphQL frameworks and tools.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>28 frameworks tested</strong>: Apollo, Hasura, PostGraphile, FraiseQL, and more
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>10 benchmark scenarios</strong>: Query complexity, N+1 queries, auth overhead, etc.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Consistent methodology</strong>: Fair comparison across different approaches
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reproducible</strong>: Docker-based test environments
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open results</strong>: All data and code published
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Why It Exists</h2>
      <p>
        GraphQL benchmarks often hide biases:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Each framework claims to be "fastest"</li>
        <li>Benchmarks test only favorable scenarios</li>
        <li>Hard to compare across different approaches</li>
        <li>Missing real-world scenarios (N+1, auth, aggregations)</li>
        <li>Unclear methodology and setup</li>
      </ul>
      <p>velocitybench provides transparent, reproducible comparison.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Benchmark Scenarios</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Simple Query</strong>: Single entity fetch (baseline)</li>
        <li><strong>Nested Query</strong>: 3-level deep nesting (joins)</li>
        <li><strong>N+1 Query</strong>: Intentional N+1 scenario (reveals resolver chains)</li>
        <li><strong>List Query</strong>: Fetch 100 items with nested relationships</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregation</strong>: Complex GROUP BY and window functions</li>
        <li><strong>Authorization</strong>: Per-field auth overhead</li>
        <li><strong>Mutation</strong>: Complex mutation with 5 related updates</li>
        <li><strong>Error Handling</strong>: Partial errors in large result sets</li>
        <li><strong>Concurrent Queries</strong>: 100 concurrent requests</li>
        <li><strong>Memory Profile</strong>: Memory under load</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Measured Metrics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Latency (p50, p95, p99)</li>
        <li>Throughput (requests/second)</li>
        <li>Memory usage (peak, average)</li>
        <li>Error rate under load</li>
        <li>CPU utilization</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Language</strong>: Rust (load generation)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Infrastructure</strong>: Docker Compose for test environments
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reporting</strong>: Interactive dashboards + CSV export
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration with Other Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>FraiseQL</strong>: Benchmarked against all other 27 frameworks
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CI/CD</strong>: Can run in automated pipelines
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>GitHub Repository</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/velocitybench" target="_blank">
          Visit velocitybench on GitHub →
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>All results, methodology, and code open source.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Related Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/fraiseql-core">fraiseql</a> – Benchmarked framework</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem">← Back to Ecosystem</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
